differences vs the shipped docs/carney_handover/polaris_demo_pubkey.asc ->
wrong fingerprint (2C2D...82C1 vs pinned FB22...0C02) -> production verifier
would always fail.

Fix: replace TRUST_ROOT_ARMORED with TRUST_ROOT_BASE64 = base64-encoded raw
bytes of the actual source file (no multi-line ASCII to mis-copy). Decoded at
runtime via Buffer.from(.., "base64") and fed to gpg --dearmor exactly as the
shipped pubkey would be.

Defense in depth: tests/scripts/test_trust_root_consts.py asserts:
1. base64-decoded TRUST_ROOT_BASE64 bytes == shipped pubkey file bytes (exact)
2. PINNED_FP == state/polaris_gpg_keyid.txt
3. gpg --show-keys on the decoded bytes parses to PINNED_FP
3/3 PASS. This class of mismatch can no longer slip through silently.

Also: cleaned the remaining iter-3 P3 stale comments in
scripts/build_canonical_demo_bundle.py (docstring + the "NO .asc" line).

Final local proof:
- pytest tests/scripts/: 69 PASSED (incl. 3 new trust-root-consts)
- python scripts/check_signed_bundles.py: rc=0
